# Google Secret Manager Version Cleanup

When updating GCP Secret Manager values for this repo, avoid retaining historical
payload versions unless rollback access is explicitly needed.

## Repo Scripts

- `scripts/setup_gcp_secrets.sh`
  - Uploads the API and ETL env bundle secrets.
  - After each successful `gcloud secrets versions add`, destroys older
    non-destroyed versions for that same secret.

- `scripts/cleanup_gcp_secret_versions.sh`
  - Scans all secrets in a project, or one secret via `--secret`.
  - Defaults to dry-run.
  - Use `--apply --yes` only when intentionally destroying older Secret Manager
    versions.

## Safety Notes

- Secret Manager version destruction is irreversible.
- Keep the newest non-destroyed version for each secret.
- Prefer a dry-run before applying cleanup across a project.
